{"title_page": "Giant's Causeway (horse)", "text_new": "{{Short description|American-bred Thoroughbred racehorse}}\n\n{{Infobox racehorse\n| horsename = Giant's Causeway\n| image = \n| caption = \n| sire = [[Storm Cat]]\n| grandsire = [[Storm Bird]]\n| dam = [[Mariah's Storm]]\n| damsire = [[Rahy]]\n| sex = [[Stallion (horse)|Stallion]]\n| foaled = 1997\n| country = United States\n| colour = [[Chestnut (coat)|Chestnut]]\n| breeder = [[Coolmore Stud|Orpendale]] & [[Michael Tabor]]\n| owner = [[Sue Magnier]] & Michael Tabor\n| trainer = [[Aidan O'Brien]]\n| record = 13: 9\u20134\u20130\n| earnings = $3,078,989\n| race = [[Futurity Stakes (Ireland)|Futurity Stakes]] (1999)<br>[[Prix de la Salamandre]] (1999)<br>[[Gladness Stakes]] (2000)<br>[[St. James's Palace Stakes]] (2000)<br>[[Eclipse Stakes]] (2000)<br>[[Sussex Stakes]] (2000)<br>[[International Stakes|Juddmonte International Stakes]] (2000)<br>[[Irish Champion Stakes]] (2000)\n|awards = [[Cartier Horse of the Year]] (2000)<br>[[Leading sire in North America]] (2009, 2010, 2012)<br> [[Leading broodmare sire in North America]] (2018)\n|honours = [[Giant's Causeway Stakes]] at [[Keeneland]]\n|updated = April 17, 2010\n}}\n\n'''Giant's Causeway''' (February 14, 1997 \u2013 April 16, 2018) was a [[Kentucky]]-bred [[thoroughbred]] [[horse racing|racehorse]] who competed primarily in [[Europe]].\n\n==Background==\nGiant's Causeway was a chestnut horse bred in Kentucky by [[Coolmore Stud|Orpendale]] & [[Michael Tabor]].\n\n==Racing career==\n===1999: two-year-old season===\nAs a two-year-old in 1999, Giant's Causeway was unbeaten in three races: a [[maiden race]] at [[Naas]], the [[Futurity Stakes (Ireland)|Futurity Stakes]] at the [[Curragh Racecourse|Curragh]] and the [[Prix de la Salamandre]] at [[Longchamp Racecourse|Longchamp]].\n\n===2000: three-year-old season===\nIn the spring of 2000, Giant's Causeway won the [[Gladness Stakes]] at the Curragh and then finished second in both the [[2000 Guineas]] and the [[Irish 2000 Guineas]].\n\nHe then won five straight [[Group races|Group One]] races: the [[St. James's Palace Stakes]] at [[Royal Ascot]], the [[Eclipse Stakes]] at [[Sandown Park]], the [[Sussex Stakes]] at [[Goodwood Racecourse|Goodwood]], the [[International Stakes|Juddmonte International Stakes]] at [[York Racecourse|York]] and the [[Irish Champion Stakes]] at [[Leopardstown Racecourse|Leopardstown]].\n\nHis winning sequence was broken in the [[Queen Elizabeth II Stakes]] at Ascot on 23 September, when he was beaten half a length by [[Observatory (horse)|Observatory]]. On his final racecourse appearance, Giant's Causeway was sent to the United States to contest the [[Breeders' Cup Classic]] at [[Churchill Downs]] in which he raced on dirt for the first time. Starting at odds of 7.6/1 he was beaten a neck into second place by the American colt [[Tiznow]], with the other beaten horses including [[Captain Steve]], [[Lemon Drop Kid]], [[Fusaichi Pegasus]] and [[Cat Thief]].\n\n==Awards==\nGiant's Causeway performance in 2000 earned him [[Cartier Horse of the Year|European Horse of the Year]] honors.\n\n==Post-Racing Career==\nIn 2001, Giant's Causeway entered [[horse breeding|stud]] at [[Coolmore Stud]] in [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]], then the following year was sent to stand at Coolmore's [[Australia]] branch.  His success led to the stallion going to Coolmore's [[United States|U.S.]] unit, [[Ashford Stud]] in [[Versailles, Kentucky]]. In 2006, he stood for a fee of $300,000.\n\nGiant's Causeway died at the Ashford Stud on 16 April 2018 after a \"brief illness\" at the age of 21.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/227030/giants-causeway-dead-at-21|title=Giant's Causeway Dead at 21|date=17 April 2018|publisher=[[The Blood-Horse]]}}</ref>\n\n==Stud career==\n\nGiant's Causeway's descendants include:<ref name=\"ACP\">{{cite web|title=Giant's Causeway|url=https://ahonoora.com/giants_causeway.html|website=Ahonoora|accessdate=7 August 2019|language=en}}</ref>\n\n''c = [[colt (horse)|colt]], f = [[filly]]''\n\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size:90%\" \n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n| style=\"width:35px;\"| '''Foaled'''\n| style=\"width:120px;\"| '''Name'''\n| style=\"width:35px;\"| '''Sex'''\n| style=\"width:580px;\"| '''Major Wins'''\n|-\n| 2002\n| [[Footstepsinthesand]] \n| c\n| [[2000 Guineas]]\n|-\n| 2002\n| [[My Typhoon]]\n| f\n| [[Diana Stakes]]\n|-\n| 2002\n| [[Maids Causeway]]\n| f\n| [[Coronation Stakes]]\n|-\n| 2002\n| [[Aragorn (horse) | Aragorn]]\n| f\n| [[Oak Tree Derby]], [[Eddie Read Stakes]], [[Shoemaker Mile Stakes]], [[Del Mar Mile Handicap]]\n|-\n| 2002\n| [[Shamardal]]\n| c\n| [[Poule d'Essai des Poulains]], [[St James's Palace Stakes]], [[Vintage Stakes]], [[Dewhurst Stakes]]\n|-\n| 2003\n| Heatseeker\n| c\n| [[Santa Anita Handicap]] \n|-\n| 2003\n| Frost Giant\n| c\n| [[Suburban Handicap]] \n|-\n| 2003\n| [[First Samurai]]\n| c\n| [[Hopeful Stakes (Japan) | Hopeful Stakes]]\n|-\n| 2004\n| [[Mike Fox (horse) | Mike Horse]]\n| c\n| [[Queen's Plate]]  \n|-\n| 2004\n| Suzuka Causeway\n| c\n| [[Keio Hai Spring Cup]]\n|-\n| 2004\n| [[Swift Temper]]\n| c\n| [[Ruffian Stakes]], [[Delaware Handicap]], [[Groupie Doll Stakes]]\n|-\n| 2004\n| [[Red Giant (horse) | Red Giant]]\n| c\n| [[Commonwealth Derby | Virginia Derby]], [[Fourstardave Handicap]], [[Clement L. Hirsch Turf Championship Stakes]]\n|-\n| 2005\n| Cowboy Cal\n| c\n| [[City of Hope Mile Stakes | Oak Tree Mile Stakes]], [[Strub Stakes]], [[San Pasqual Handicap]], [[Bryan Station Stakes]]\n|-\n| 2006\n| [[Ghanaati]]\n| c\n| [[1000 Guineas Stakes]]\n|-\n| 2007\n| Eishin Apollon\n| f\n| [[Mile Championship]]\n|-\n| 2007\n| Await the Dawn\n| f\n| [[Hardwicke Stakes]], [[Kilternan Stakes]]\n|-\n| 2007\n| [[Eskendereya]]\n| f\n| [[Wood Memorial Stakes]], [[Pilgrim Stakes]], [[Fountain of Youth Stakes]]\n|-\n| 2009\n| Creative Cause\n| c\n| [[American Pharoah Stakes]], [[San Felipe Stakes]]\n