{"title_page": "Mid and South Essex NHS Foundation Trust", "text_new": "{{Short description|NHS foundation trust based in Essex, England}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Use British English|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox NHS organisation\n| name             = Mid and South Essex NHS Foundation Trust\n| native_name      = \n| native_name_lang = \n| former_name      = \n| logo             = Mid and South Essex NHS Foundation Trust.svg\n| logo_alt         = \n| logo_size        = \n| logo_caption     = \n| logo_padding     = \n| image            = \n| image_alt        = \n| image_size       = \n| image_caption    = \n| map              = \n| map_size         = \n| map_alt          = \n| map_caption      = \n| start_date       = 1 April 2020\n| foundation_date  = \n| end_date         = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} -->\n| headquarters     = \n| coords           = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LON|type:landmark_region:GB|display=inline,title}} -->\n| region_served    = \n| nhs_region       = \n| area             = \n| population       = \n| establishments   = \n| type             = [[NHS foundation trust]]\n| budget           =  \n| hospitals        = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Basildon University Hospital]]\n* [[Braintree Community Hospital]]\n* [[Broomfield Hospital]]\n* [[Southend University Hospital]]\n* [[St Peter's Hospital, Maldon|St Peter's Hospital]]\n}}\n| beds             = \n| chair            = \n| chief_exec       = \n| staff            = 12,000+ \n| website          =\n}}\n'''Mid and South Essex NHS Foundation Trust''' is a new [[NHS foundation trust]] running three major hospitals across Essex, [[Southend University Hospital]], [[Basildon University Hospital]], and [[Broomfield Hospital]].<ref name=\"HSJ\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hsj.co.uk/basildon-and-thurrock-university-hospitals-nhs-foundation-trust/two-execs-step-down-as-mega-merger-trusts-rebrand/7025450.article|title=Two execs step down as mega-merger trusts rebrand|publisher=HSJ|date = 25 February 2019 | first= James |last=Illman}}</ref> It was formed on 1st April 2020 from the amalgamation of 3 existing trusts, [[Mid Essex Hospital Services NHS Trust]], [[Basildon and Thurrock University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust]], and [[Southend University Hospital NHS Foundation Trust]]. The Trust also manages smaller sites including Braintree Hospital.\n\nOne of the biggest NHS Trusts in the country, Mid and South Essex NHS Foundation Trust serves a population of 1.2 million people<ref name=\"MEHT\">{{cite news |title=Mid and South Essex University Hospitals Group CEO comments on IRP decision|url=https://www.meht.nhs.uk/news/july/mid-and-south-essex-university-hospitals-group-ceo-comments-on-irp-decision/ |publisher=[[Mid Essex Hospital Services NHS Trust]] |date= 31 July 2019}}</ref> and has an annual revenue of over \u00a3850m.<ref name=\"HSJ\" />\n\n== History ==\nAn initial merger between the 3 trusts was first agreed in January 2018.<ref>{{cite news |title=Basildon, Southend and Broomfield hospitals back merger plans |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-essex-42625456 |publisher=BBC News |date=10 January 2018}}</ref> This came after a number of proposals from the Mid and South Essex Sustainability and Transformation Partnership (STP) regarding reconfiguring services provided in the area.\n\nIn October 2018 the plan was referred by [[Southend-on-Sea Borough Council]] to the [[Secretary of State for Health and Social Care]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Southend Council refers \u00a3118m plan for Southend, Basildon and Broomfield hospitals to health secretary |url=https://www.echo-news.co.uk/news/16972648.southend-council-refers-118m-plan-for-southend-basildon-and-broomfield-hospitals-to-health-secretary/ |publisher=Echo News |date=10 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 July 2019 the [[Secretary of State for Health and Social Care]] endorsed the merger and a provisional date of 1 April 2020 was agreed.<ref name=\"MEHT\" />\n\nOn 1 April 2020 the trusts formally merged adopting the new title of Mid and South Essex NHS Foundation Trust, amid the COVID-19 pandemic.\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of hospitals in Essex]]\n*[[Healthcare in Essex]]\n*[[List of NHS trusts]]\n*[[Southend University Hospital NHS Foundation Trust]]\n*[[Basildon and Thurrock University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust]]\n*[[Mid Essex Hospital Services NHS Trust]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.southend.nhs.uk/ Southend Hospital]\n*[http://www.basildonandthurrock.nhs.uk/ Basildon Hospital]\n*[http://www.meht.nhs.uk/ Mid Essex Hospital]\n\n{{Mid and South Essex NHS Foundation Trust}}\n\n[[Category:NHS foundation trusts]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in Essex]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|NHS foundation trust based in Essex, England}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Use British English|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox NHS organisation\n| name             = Mid and South Essex NHS Foundation Trust\n| native_name      = \n| native_name_lang = \n| former_name      = \n| logo             = Mid and South Essex NHS Foundation Trust.svg\n| logo_alt         = \n| logo_size        = \n| logo_caption     = \n| logo_padding     = \n| image            = \n| image_alt        = \n| image_size       = \n| image_caption    = \n| map              = \n| map_size         = \n| map_alt          = \n| map_caption      = \n| start_date       = 1 April 2020\n| foundation_date  = \n| end_date         = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} -->\n| headquarters     = \n| coords           = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LON|type:landmark_region:GB|display=inline,title}} -->\n| region_served    = \n| nhs_region       = \n| area             = \n| population       = \n| establishments   = \n| type             = [[NHS foundation trust]]\n| budget           =  \n| hospitals        = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Basildon University Hospital]]\n* [[Broomfield Hospital]]\n* [[Southend University Hospital]]\n* [[St Peter's Hospital, Maldon|St Peter's Hospital]]\n}}\n| beds             = \n| chair            = \n| chief_exec       = \n| staff            = 12,000+ \n| website          =\n}}\n'''Mid and South Essex NHS Foundation Trust''' is a new [[NHS foundation trust]] running three major hospitals across Essex, [[Southend University Hospital]], [[Basildon University Hospital]], and [[Broomfield Hospital]].<ref name=\"HSJ\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hsj.co.uk/basildon-and-thurrock-university-hospitals-nhs-foundation-trust/two-execs-step-down-as-mega-merger-trusts-rebrand/7025450.article|title=Two execs step down as mega-merger trusts rebrand|publisher=HSJ|date = 25 February 2019 | first= James |last=Illman}}</ref> It was formed on 1st April 2020 from the amalgamation of 3 existing trusts, [[Mid Essex Hospital Services NHS Trust]], [[Basildon and Thurrock University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust]], and [[Southend University Hospital NHS Foundation Trust]]. The Trust also manages smaller sites including Braintree Hospital.\n\nOne of the biggest NHS Trusts in the country, Mid and South Essex NHS Foundation Trust serves a population of 1.2 million people<ref name=\"MEHT\">{{cite news |title=Mid and South Essex University Hospitals Group CEO comments on IRP decision|url=https://www.meht.nhs.uk/news/july/mid-and-south-essex-university-hospitals-group-ceo-comments-on-irp-decision/ |publisher=[[Mid Essex Hospital Services NHS Trust]] |date= 31 July 2019}}</ref> and has an annual revenue of over \u00a3850m.<ref name=\"HSJ\" />\n\n== History ==\nAn initial merger between the 3 trusts was first agreed in January 2018.<ref>{{cite news |title=Basildon, Southend and Broomfield hospitals back merger plans |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-essex-42625456 |publisher=BBC News |date=10 January 2018}}</ref> This came after a number of proposals from the Mid and South Essex Sustainability and Transformation Partnership (STP) regarding reconfiguring services provided in the area.\n\nIn October 2018 the plan was referred by [[Southend-on-Sea Borough Council]] to the [[Secretary of State for Health and Social Care]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Southend Council refers \u00a3118m plan for Southend, Basildon and Broomfield hospitals to health secretary |url=https://www.echo-news.co.uk/news/16972648.southend-council-refers-118m-plan-for-southend-basildon-and-broomfield-hospitals-to-health-secretary/ |publisher=Echo News |date=10 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 July 2019 the [[Secretary of State for Health and Social Care]] endorsed the merger and a provisional date of 1 April 2020 was agreed.<ref name=\"MEHT\" />\n\nOn 1 April 2020 the trusts formally merged adopting the new title of Mid and South Essex NHS Foundation Trust, amid the COVID-19 pandemic.\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of hospitals in Essex]]\n*[[Healthcare in Essex]]\n*[[List of NHS trusts]]\n*[[Southend University Hospital NHS Foundation Trust]]\n*[[Basildon and Thurrock University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust]]\n*[[Mid Essex Hospital Services NHS Trust]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.southend.nhs.uk/ Southend Hospital]\n*[http://www.basildonandthurrock.nhs.uk/ Basildon Hospital]\n*[http://www.meht.nhs.uk/ Mid Essex Hospital]\n\n{{Mid and South Essex NHS Foundation Trust}}\n\n[[Category:NHS foundation trusts]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in Essex]]\n", "name_user": "Admiral Rolland", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added Braintree to infobox", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mid_and_South_Essex_NHS_Foundation_Trust"}
