{"title_page": "Nudnik", "text_new": "'''''Nudnik''''' was a [[Czechoslovakia|Czechoslovak]]/[[Czech Republic|Czech]] [[animated film]] series directed by [[Gene Deitch]], produced by [[William L. Snyder|William Lawrence Snyder]], and distributed by [[Paramount Pictures|Paramount Studios]]. Twelve shorts were released during 1965 and 1967. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fantagraphics.com/flog/nudnik-revealed-by-gene-deitch-cover-excerpt/|title=Nudnik Revealed! by Gene Deitch - Cover & Excerpt|date=August 6, 2013}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cartoonresearch.com/index.php/book-review-nudnik-revealed/|title=Book Review: \u201cNudnik Revealed!\u201d &#124;|website=cartoonresearch.com}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.awn.com/animationworld/self-help-nudnik-part-2|title=Self-Help for Nudnik \u2014 Part 2|website=Animation World Network}}</ref> His cartoons would go on to be syndicated around 1991. The character's tagline is \"Whatever can go wrong with NUDNIK, will go wrong.\"\n\nThe first cartoon of the series \"Here's Nudnik\", (originally called Nudnik #2) was nominated for the [[Academy Award for Best Animated Short Film]] in 1965<ref name=\"Oscars1965\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/1965 |title=The 37th Academy Awards (1965) Nominees and Winners |accessdate=June 1, 2019|work=oscars.org}}</ref> . \n\n==Synopsis==\n''Nudnik'' contains only one major character, simply named Nudnik (or, Yaramaz Nudnik, as the Turkish DVDs refer to him). He can't do anything right; when he does something, it usually ends with disastrous results, and usually gets him in trouble. At first the idea was for each short to be scored with melancholy jazz music, which was done for the first cartoon. However, the studio wasn't pleased with the musical choice, and they made Gene use more upbeat music. The song that was used most often was \"[[Wrap_Your_Troubles_in_Dreams_(song)|Wrap Your Troubles In Dreams]]\", used both for the opening sequence and as a general theme of sorts for the character himself.\n\nThough there were other characters, they were unnamed, such as the fat woman, the dog, the cop, and the thief. It was sort of an unspoken rule that everything in the world hates Nudnik, further adding to the mayhem.\n\n==Shorts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Title !! Release Date !! Alternate Title\n|-\n| 01 - '''''Here's Nudnik''''' || August 1, 1965 || ''Nudnik #2''\n|-\n| 02 - '''''Drive On, Nudnik''''' || November 1965|| None\n|-\n| 03 - '''''Home Sweet Nudnik''''' || March 1966 || None\n|-\n| 04 - '''''Nudnik on a Shoestring''''' || March 12, 1966 || None\n|-\n| 05 - '''''Welcome, Nudnik'''' || May 1966 || None\n|-\n| 06 - '''''Nudnik on the Roof''''' || July 1966 || None\n|-\n| 07 - '''''From Nudnik with Love''''' || September 1966 || None\n|-\n| 08 - '''''Nudnik On A Showcase''''' || Jan 1967 || None\n|-\n| 09 - '''''Nowhere With Nudnik''''' || March 1967 || None\n|-\n| 10 - '''''Goodnight Sweet Nudnik''''' || April 1967 || None\n|-\n| 11 - '''''Who Needs Nudnik??''''' || May 1967 || None\n|-\n| 12 - '''''Nudnik on the Beach''''' || May 1967 || None\n|-\n| 13 - '''''Good Neighbor Nudnik''''' || June 1967 || None\n|-\n| 14 - '''''Nudnik's Nudnickel''''' || August 1967 || None\n|-\n| 15 - '''''I Remember Nudnik''''' || September 1967 || None\n|}\n\n==TV series==\nA 'new' animated series, ''The Nudnik Show'', was created in 1991, which showed the 12 classic shorts in syndication, and it also had one brand new Nudnik short, \"Nudnik Impossible\", however it was mostly made using left over clips from old promotional material from when the shorts were original being produced in the 60s, bringing the number of Nudnik shorts from 12 to 13. \nIt also had 11 bumpers with all new animation, each one being about 30 seconds long, according to the IMDb listing, [[Jules Feiffer]] was a writer for the series, so it is most likely that he wrote for the bumpers. The production companies were [[Paramount Pictures]] and of course [[Rembrandt Films]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0299359/|title=The Nudnik Show|accessdate=Jul 11, 2019|via=www.imdb.com}}</ref>\n\nThe shorts were featured on [[Cartoon Network]]'s animated anthology series ''[[ToonHeads]]'' in 1996.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1996-01-07/news/tv-21992_1_cartoon-network|title=SHOWS FOR YOUNGSTERS AND THEIR PARENTS TOO : At last, 'Nudnik' emerges from storage onto the Cartoon Network|first=N.F.|last=Mendoza|date=January 7, 1996|work=[[The New York Times]]|publisher=[[The New York Times Company]]|accessdate=2013-04-28}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|id=0215126|name=Gene Deitch}}\n* {{bcdb |Other_Studios/R/Rembrandt_Films/Nudnik/|Nudnik}}\n* Translation of the name/word [https://translate.google.com/#auto|en|yaramaz \"Yaramaz\"]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nudnik (Cartoon)}}\n[[Category:Czech animated television series]]\n[[Category:Animated comedy films]]\n[[Category:Animated film series]]\n[[Category:Film series introduced in 1965]]\n[[Category:Male characters in animation]]\n\n\n{{animation-tv-prog-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''''Nudnik''''' was a [[Czechoslovakia|Czechoslovak]]/[[Czech Republic|Czech]] [[animated film]] series directed by [[Gene Deitch]], produced by [[William L. Snyder|William Lawrence Snyder]], and distributed by [[Paramount Pictures|Paramount Studios]]. Twelve shorts were released during 1965 and 1967. <ref>http://fantagraphics.com/flog/nudnik-revealed-by-gene-deitch-cover-excerpt/</ref> <ref>https://cartoonresearch.com/index.php/book-review-nudnik-revealed/</ref> <ref>https://www.awn.com/animationworld/self-help-nudnik-part-2</ref> His cartoons would go on to be syndicated around 1991. The character's tagline is \"Whatever can go wrong with NUDNIK, will go wrong.\"\n\nThe first cartoon of the series \"Here's Nudnik\", (originally called Nudnik #2) was nominated for the [[Academy Award for Best Animated Short Film]] in 1965<ref name=\"Oscars1965\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/1965 |title=The 37th Academy Awards (1965) Nominees and Winners |accessdate=June 1, 2019|work=oscars.org}}</ref> . \n\n==Synopsis==\n''Nudnik'' contains only one major character, simply named Nudnik (or, Yaramaz Nudnik, as the Turkish DVDs refer to him). He can't do anything right; when he does something, it usually ends with disastrous results, and usually gets him in trouble. At first the idea was for each short to be scored with melancholy jazz music, which was done for the first cartoon. However, the studio wasn't pleased with the musical choice, and they made Gene use more upbeat music. The song that was used most often was \"[[Wrap_Your_Troubles_in_Dreams_(song)|Wrap Your Troubles In Dreams]]\", used both for the opening sequence and as a general theme of sorts for the character himself.\n\nThough there were other characters, they were unnamed, such as the fat woman, the dog, the cop, and the thief. It was sort of an unspoken rule that everything in the world hates Nudnik, further adding to the mayhem.\n\n==Shorts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Title !! Release Date !! Alternate Title\n|-\n| 01 - '''''Here's Nudnik''''' || August 1, 1965 || ''Nudnik #2''\n|-\n| 02 - '''''Drive On, Nudnik''''' || November 1965|| None\n|-\n| 03 - '''''Home Sweet Nudnik''''' || March 1966 || None\n|-\n| 04 - '''''Nudnik on a Shoestring''''' || March 12, 1966 || None\n|-\n| 05 - '''''Welcome, Nudnik'''' || May 1966 || None\n|-\n| 06 - '''''Nudnik on the Roof''''' || July 1966 || None\n|-\n| 07 - '''''From Nudnik with Love''''' || September 1966 || None\n|-\n| 08 - '''''Nudnik On A Showcase''''' || Jan 1967 || None\n|-\n| 09 - '''''Nowhere With Nudnik''''' || March 1967 || None\n|-\n| 10 - '''''Goodnight Sweet Nudnik''''' || April 1967 || None\n|-\n| 11 - '''''Who Needs Nudnik??''''' || May 1967 || None\n|-\n| 12 - '''''Nudnik on the Beach''''' || May 1967 || None\n|-\n| 13 - '''''Good Neighbor Nudnik''''' || June 1967 || None\n|-\n| 14 - '''''Nudnik's Nudnickel''''' || August 1967 || None\n|-\n| 15 - '''''I Remember Nudnik''''' || September 1967 || None\n|}\n\n==TV series==\nA 'new' animated series, ''The Nudnik Show'', was created in 1991, which showed the 12 classic shorts in syndication, and it also had one brand new Nudnik short, \"Nudnik Impossible\", however it was mostly made using left over clips from old promotional material from when the shorts were original being produced in the 60s, bringing the number of Nudnik shorts from 12 to 13. \nIt also had 11 bumpers with all new animation, each one being about 30 seconds long, according to the IMDb listing, [[Jules Feiffer]] was a writer for the series, so it is most likely that he wrote for the bumpers. The production companies were [[Paramount Pictures]] and of course [[Rembrandt Films]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0299359/|title=The Nudnik Show|accessdate=Jul 11, 2019|via=www.imdb.com}}</ref>\n\nThe shorts were featured on [[Cartoon Network]]'s animated anthology series ''[[ToonHeads]]'' in 1996.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1996-01-07/news/tv-21992_1_cartoon-network|title=SHOWS FOR YOUNGSTERS AND THEIR PARENTS TOO : At last, 'Nudnik' emerges from storage onto the Cartoon Network|first=N.F.|last=Mendoza|date=January 7, 1996|work=[[The New York Times]]|publisher=[[The New York Times Company]]|accessdate=2013-04-28}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|id=0215126|name=Gene Deitch}}\n* {{bcdb |Other_Studios/R/Rembrandt_Films/Nudnik/|Nudnik}}\n* Translation of the name/word [https://translate.google.com/#auto|en|yaramaz \"Yaramaz\"]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nudnik (Cartoon)}}\n[[Category:Czech animated television series]]\n[[Category:Animated comedy films]]\n[[Category:Animated film series]]\n[[Category:Film series introduced in 1965]]\n[[Category:Male characters in animation]]\n\n\n{{animation-tv-prog-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Discospinster", "